    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/261">Chuonradus</persName> dei gratia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> excellentissimus secundum voluntatem dei
                        salvatoris nostrique liberatoris. Quicquid confirmationis et proprietatis ad
                        ecclesiarum dei sanctorumque suorum exaltatione prebuerimus, id nobis ad
                        aeterne beatitudinis bravium et secularis vitae profectum esse profuturum
                        verissime credimus. Igitur omnium sanctae dei aecclesiae fidelium
                        nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac futurorum agnoscat universitas, qualiter
                        nos pro dei omnipotentis amore et pro anima amitae nostre <persName
                            key="#Queen" ref="#people/1301">Adheleidis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Queen">imperatricis</rs> augustae et ob remedium animae nostre
                        parentumque nostrorum, rogante domno <persName key="#Abbots"><name
                                ref="Maurus">Mauro</name></persName> venerabili <rs key="#Abbots"
                                    >abbate</rs>, suo <rs key="#Monasteries">cenobio</rs> ad honore <orgName
                                        key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Offersio/donatio #Rivers #Mountains #Villas #Curtes #Massae #Mansi #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Saltworks #Penalty #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Castle #Angaria #Teloneum #Immunity #Exemption #Churches #Monasteries #Abbots #Monks #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius"
                                        ref="#juridical_persons/3619">sancti
                            Salvatoris</orgName> haud procul a menibus <placeName ref="#places/65"
                            >Ticinensis</placeName> urbis fundato per hoc nostrum regale preceptum,
                        prout iuste et legaliter valemus, confirmamus, quemadmodum ad antecessores
                        meos preceptali auctoritate confirmata sunt, omniaque eiusdem venerabili
                        loco donata collata et oblata sunt tam de <rs key="#Offersio/donatio"
                            >largifluo dono</rs> memoratae amite nostre quam etiam aliqua
                        inscriptione cartarum aliorum hominum, cum <rs key="#Castle">castellis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Curtes">cortibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_slave">ancillis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_aldius">aldianibus</rs> et <rs key="#Royal_aldius"
                            >aldianis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">capellis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">oratoriis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Villas">villis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mansi">mansis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Landed_possessions">campis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mountains">montibus</rs> vallibus planiciebus <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Fisheries">piscationibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs> terris cultis et incultis <rs
                            key="#Tolls #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Ports">portibus</rs>, verum etiam cum omnibus, de quibus
                        venerabili coenobium iuste investituram habet vel habuit ex ea die, qua
                        prefata serenissima imperatrix <rs key="#Monks">monachos</rs> ibi
                        constituit. Confirmamus quidem et firmissimam traditionem largimur eidem
                        monasterio domini Salvatoris <rs key="#Monasteries"> monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >sancti Anastasii</orgName> una cum <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/139"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/342">Olonna</placeName></geogName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Montecelli</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Aufenengo</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Erbaria</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Basiligutiam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Frisinariam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pastorianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Riuoceruinum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Tullianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Puizolum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Centascum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Noue</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Urba</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/18">Marinco</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Corianum</placeName> cum omnibus pertitentiis suis, <rs key="#Castle"
                            >castellum</rs> da <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Bosco</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Felegariolo</placeName>, terram de <persName
                            key="#Landed_possessions
                                #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <name ref="Petrus Albesanus">Petro Albesano</name></persName>, terram
                        quam tenuit <persName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><name ref="Liudualdus">Liutaldus</name></persName> cum <rs
                            key="#Mansi">manso</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <geogName key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Pelenzona</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Armentaria</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Blundi</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Gagio</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Lagussianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Cassina</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Cuguzuda</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Garlascum</placeName> cum <rs key="#Other_administrative_unit"
                            >districtum</rs> in circuitu duo miliarium una cum <rs key="#Forests"
                            >silva</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Carbonaria</placeName>, de quantum iam dictum monasterium per preceptum
                        tenere videtur, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cauconate</placeName>, <rs>viridiarium</rs> prope Palatinam portam et
                        sancti Iohannis situm cum omnibus pertinentiis et adiacentiis suis tam infra
                        civitatem Ticinensem quam extra, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Garfiniana</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Uicolongo</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Bissione</placeName>, <rs key="#Churches">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >sancti Nazarii</orgName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Uirgemini</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Mauratica</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Melaria</placeName>. Insuper monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sancte dei genitricis Mariae</orgName> in
                        loco <placeName ref="#places/4179">Ponposa</placeName> constructum, eum
                        quibus ad eum pertinere vi videtur, vel etiam omnes <rs key="#Saltworks"
                            >salinas</rs>, quam in <placeName key="#Saltworks" ref="#places/485"
                            >Comaclo</placeName> ab supra scripto monasterio domini Salvatoris
                        pertinere decernitur, seu in aliis omnibus locis, que iam dicto coenobio
                        sancti Salvatoris pertinere cernuntur, illo in proprium corroboramus.
                        Precipientes itaque iubemus, ut <rs key="#Immunity #Exemption">nullus episcopus dux marchio comes vicecomes
                        castaldius nullaque regni nostri magna parvaque persona
                            de rebus mobilibus sive immobilibus sive de qualibet terra disvestire
                            idem monasterium sine legali iuditio presumat</rs>. Sancimus insuper et
                        hac nostra regali auctoritate concedimus, ut, si contigerit, quod sepe
                        accidit, quatinus <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> prenominati monasterii huius
                        lucis habitaculum deserat, liceat <rs key="#Monks">monachos</rs> ex sinu
                        eiusdem aecclesie quem meliorem viderint eligere in patrem, omnium
                        episcoporum vel omnium mortalium contradictione remota, nec fas sit alicui
                        monacho ex alio monasterio ad id transitum facere sine voluntate monachorum
                        inibi deo servientium in perpetuum. Si quis autem huius nostrae promulgate
                        auctoritatis et preceptis violator extiterit sive predicte aecclesie sancti
                        Salvatoris minorationem facere aut in castellis villis vel aliquibuslibet
                        locis eius aribergare, <rs key="#Assembly">placitum</rs> sine eiusdem
                        coenobii abbatis iussione ullatenus tenere aut aliquam <rs key="#Angaria"
                            >angariam</rs> vel publicam functionem aut <rs key="#Teloneum"
                            >theloneum</rs> extorquere vel tollere aut monachos de aliqua re
                        presumpserit molestare, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri cocti
                            libras mille</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere
                            nostrae</rs> ac <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem
                            abbati</rs> eiusdem monasterii qui pro tempore fuerit, et insuper, quod
                        ei deterius est, cum Iuda traditore domini salvatoris nostri, in cuius
                        nomine iam dictum monasterium constructum est, eternis deputetur incendiis.
                        Ut autem verius credatur hoc preceptum nostra auctoritate peractum,
                        presentem paginam manu propria, ut videtur infra, corroborante sigillo
                        nostro iussimus insigniri. Signum domni Chuonradi (M.) serenissimi regis.
                            <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Hugo">Hugo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice domni <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Archbishops" ref="#people/2127"
                            >Haribonis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovit. (SI. D.) Datum anno dominicae
                        incarnationis mileximo XXVI, indicione VIIII, regni vero domni Chuonradi
                        secundi regnantis II; actum <placeName key="#places/43"
                            >Placentiae</placeName>; feliciter.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
